I’m very grateful for certain books, stories, movies, archetypes, individuals and groups that helped influence me. Everybody I’ve trained with or competed against has played a part in my development. Explore and pursue the things that you connect and resonate with. Search for meaning over happiness. Meaning gives an internal cohesive structure that is substantial that can serve to fuel an individual long-term. Happiness is always fleeting. The sports I played growing up like soccer and the many life experiences which included successes and failures all played countless parts to form me and make me who I am today. So the idea that anybody is self-made or that I personally am self-made in any way, is a farce. Instead of trying to be “self-made” or claim you are such, just try being “self-committed” to your path and find your people. I find this can be a solid and simple way for leading you towards meaning.

Who is Salvatore Sanguinetti?

Salvatore Sanguinetti is 2nd degree Jiu Jitsu black belt and the founder/head coach of Guardian Gym Peru (@guardianperujj).

From a young age, Salvatore walked and slept on the streets of Peru alone. He witnessed rough events of the surrounding environment and constantly fought off hunger.

At 15, he found a mentor who helped him get into school and stay away from the “dark side” of crime/drugs. When he was a young adult, he went to America and visited his cousin, Jiu Jitsu black belt and former UFC fighter: @keithflorian and @kennyflorian. With the help of his cousin, Salvatore discovered and fell in love with Jiu Jitsu.

Salvatore was interested in all that the grappling art had to offer on the mats, but also saw how it affected people off the mats. People escaped the hardships of life through training. As a result of their training, they usually also saw improvements in these same hardships and emotional  troubles. He wanted to bring Jiu Jitsu back to Peru, so that the youth there can experience these same benefits.

Too much of the youth in Peru turns down the dark path, due to a lack of positive influences in their area. Salvatore looks to change this and provide a similar solution to what his mentor and his cousin provided for him: an opportunity. Teaming up with Guardian Gym (@guardiangym), Jiu Jitsu training is provided at zero cost to the children and their families.

When students come to train, everyone is all smiles and positive energy! Laughing and learning, the kids are inspired by their coach to train hard, despite the individual situations and hardships they face.

As one of the few positive influences in the community, Coach Salvatore is not only a Jiu Jitsu instructor. He is a life mentor and friend to his students. He helps with the situations they face at home: abuse, domestic violence, and much more. He is constantly communicating with the families of the students, to ensure they are all doing well outside of the gym.
